{
  "texts": [
    "There is an equivalenceHomog 𝑑 (Sp 𝜔, Sp) Q ≃ Mod Fun * (Sp 𝜔,Sp) Q (𝐷 𝑑 ℎ S),of ∞-categories.Remark 6.6.",
    "There is a priori no reason for this result to hold integrally: 𝐷 𝑑 is not a symmetric monoidal endofunctor of Fun * (Sp 𝜔, Sp) since 𝐷 𝑑 does not preserve the symmetric monoidal unit of Fun * (Sp 𝜔, Sp).",
    "The functor 𝐷 𝑑 ℎ S is an idempotent coalgebra object in Fun * (Sp 𝜔, Sp) since the colocalization 𝐷 𝑑: Exc 𝑑 * (Sp 𝜔, Sp) → Homog 𝑑 (Sp 𝜔, Sp) is smashing, i.e., given by Day convolution with 𝐷 𝑑 ℎ S. In the rational setting, the identification of 𝐷 𝑑 ℎ S with the localization of 𝑃 𝑑 ℎ S at the idempotent 𝑒 𝑑 induces an idempotent algebra structure on 𝐷 𝑑 ℎ S which is compatible with the idempotent coalgebra structure.",
    "This algebra structure cannot lift to an integral algebra structure as if it did, the splitting of Theorem 6.4 would also hold integrally.7.",
    "An algebraic model for rational excisive functors One of the major theorems of Goodwillie calculus is the classification of homogeneous functors."
  ]
}